Others: Yoshinobu Yamamoto pitched five innings without allowing a run in Game 5 of the NLDS, turning a potential bullpen game into a standout performance.
Yamamoto's performance came after a poor showing in Game 1 of the series, where he allowed five runs in three innings.
Teammate Kiké Hernández invited Yamamoto out for a conversation, which reportedly lasted about two hours.
Yamamoto's performance was praised by Dodgers controlling owner Mark Walter, who noted that Yamamoto'showed up tonight'.
